<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Developer Letter - v0.4</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Orbitron:wght@400;700;900&family=Inter:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    body {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
      color: #e2e8f0;
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }
    .letter-container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 2rem auto;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.8);
      border-radius: 12px;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.2);
    }
    .letter-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
      border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.5);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .letter-header h1 {
      font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin: 0;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366f1 0%, #8b5cf6 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }
    .letter-meta {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 2rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: #94a3b8;
    }
    .letter-content h2 {
      font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
      color: #6366f1;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
    .letter-content h3 {
      color: #8b5cf6;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
    .letter-content p {
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: #cbd5e1;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .letter-content ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding-left: 0;
    }
    .letter-content ul li {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      position: relative;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .letter-content ul li:before {
      content: "▸";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: #6366f1;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .letter-content ol {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      color: #cbd5e1;
    }
    .letter-content ol li {
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .highlight-box {
      background: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.1);
      border-left: 4px solid #6366f1;
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .highlight-box strong {
      color: #6366f1;
    }
    .tech-stack {
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6);
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    .letter-footer {
      margin-top: 3rem;
      padding-top: 2rem;
      border-top: 2px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.5);
      text-align: center;
      font-style: italic;
      color: #94a3b8;
    }
    .signature {
      font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      color: #6366f1;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .back-button {
      display: inline-block;
      margin: 2rem auto;
      padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366f1 0%, #8b5cf6 100%);
      color: white;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .back-button:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.4);
    }
    .button-container {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../partials/header', { user: user }) %>

  <div class="letter-container">
    <div class="letter-header">
      <h1>Developer Letter - v0.4</h1>
      <div class="letter-meta">
        <span>October 26, 2025</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>Version 0.4.0 "Foundation Arc"</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>The Stringborn Team</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="letter-content">
      <h2>Greetings, Travelers</h2>

      <p>Welcome to the v0.4 "Foundation Arc" update for Stringborn Universe. This release marks a significant milestone in our journey toward creating a fully player-governed, distributed MMO where your creativity shapes the universe.</p>

      <h3>The Vision</h3>

      <p>Stringborn Universe isn't just another game—it's an experiment in collaborative world-building. We're constructing a persistent universe where:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Players create the content</strong> through our integrated pixel art asset builder</li>
        <li><strong>Community governance</strong> determines what enters the universe via democratic voting</li>
        <li><strong>Real-time systems</strong> enable synchronous multiplayer experiences across a shared galactic map</li>
        <li><strong>Transparent development</strong> allows you to see exactly how the universe operates</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What We've Built (So Far)</h3>

      <p>Over the past weeks, we've been deep in the trenches building the foundational systems that make this vision possible. Here's what's now operational:</p>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>Core Infrastructure</strong>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Galactic Map System:</strong> A live, synchronized territory navigator showing faction control and player positions in real-time</li>
          <li><strong>Character Management:</strong> Full character creation with talent trees, equipment loadouts, and progression tracking</li>
          <li><strong>Asset Workshop:</strong> An integrated pixel editor allowing you to design sprites, items, and environmental assets</li>
          <li><strong>Voting Protocol:</strong> Democratic asset approval system where the community decides what gets added to the universe</li>
          <li><strong>Socket Synchronization:</strong> Real-time websocket infrastructure keeping all players in sync</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>Technical Achievements</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>Advanced scatter/repulsion algorithms for natural character positioning</li>
          <li>Persistent game state management across server restarts</li>
          <li>Multi-layer UI system with proper z-indexing and interaction handling</li>
          <li>Admin tester toolkit for rapid development and debugging</li>
          <li>Comprehensive inventory system with ship and character storage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3>The Road Ahead</h3>

      <p>v0.4 is a <strong>foundation</strong>. We're intentionally shipping early and often, gathering feedback from our pioneer community to shape what comes next.</p>

      <p><strong>Coming Soon:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Zone exploration and discovery mechanics</li>
        <li>Combat and skill systems</li>
        <li>Player-driven economy and trading</li>
        <li>Faction warfare with territory conquest</li>
        <li>Environmental storytelling through the Tome (lore database)</li>
        <li>Mobile-responsive interface</li>
        <li>Enhanced social features (guilds, parties, messaging)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>We Need You</h3>

      <p>This is where you come in. We're building Stringborn <strong>with</strong> you, not just <strong>for</strong> you. Here's how you can contribute:</p>

      <ol>
        <li><strong>Create Assets:</strong> Use the Asset Workshop to design items, characters, or environmental pieces</li>
        <li><strong>Vote on Content:</strong> Help curate what enters the universe through the voting system</li>
        <li><strong>Test & Report:</strong> Break things, find bugs, and tell us what doesn't feel right</li>
        <li><strong>Share Ideas:</strong> Join the conversation about features, mechanics, and direction</li>
        <li><strong>Spread the Word:</strong> Invite fellow creators who share this vision</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>A Word on Bugs</h3>

      <p>You will encounter bugs. Systems will break. Features will feel incomplete. This is expected and intentional—we're building in public, iterating rapidly based on real usage. Every bug report, every piece of feedback, every suggestion helps us build something better.</p>

      <h3>Technical Philosophy</h3>

      <p>For those curious about our technical approach:</p>

      <div class="tech-stack">
        • Node.js/Express backend with MongoDB for persistent data<br>
        • Socket.io for real-time synchronization<br>
        • Canvas-based rendering for the galactic map and pixel art systems<br>
        • EJS templating for server-rendered views<br>
        • Passport authentication with session management<br>
        • Community-driven content pipeline with voting and moderation tools
      </div>

      <p>We believe in transparency. Our architecture is designed to eventually support federation and distributed hosting—the endgame is a truly decentralized MMO that no single entity controls.</p>

      <h3>Thank You</h3>

      <p>To everyone who's already jumped in, created characters, submitted assets, and provided feedback—<strong>thank you</strong>. You're the pioneers building the foundation of something unprecedented.</p>

      <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem; color: #6366f1;">This is just the beginning.</p>

      <div class="letter-footer">
        <p>See you in the universe,</p>
        <div class="signature">— The Stringborn Team</div>
        <p style="margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 0.875rem;">
          Questions? Feedback? Find us through the in-game contact systems or community channels.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #64748b;">
          This letter will be preserved as part of Stringborn's historical development record.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="button-container">
      <a href="/menu" class="back-button">← Back to Navigation Hub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
